   Unidentified assailants hurled a grenade and fired shots today at the home of relatives of Nelson Mandela, killing a baby girl and injuring her parents, police said.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   An ANC statement said, ``The ANC notes the curious coincidence of an attack on a man bearing the Mandela name at this time''.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   Given the distant connection between Mandela and the family, police said they did not know if the attack was deliberate or just a random attack linked to the general violence.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   Mandela and other ANC leaders have been negotiating with President F.W. de Klerk to pave the way for full-scale talks on ending apartheid, the South African system of racial separation.
  </a>
